.TH "dpni_set_single_step_cfg" 9 "dpni_set_single_step_cfg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dpni_set_single_step_cfg \- enable/disable and configure single step PTP
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dpni_set_single_step_cfg
.BI "(struct fsl_mc_io *mc_io "  ","
.BI "u32 cmd_flags "  ","
.BI "u16 token "  ","
.BI "struct dpni_single_step_cfg *ptp_cfg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mc_io" 12
Pointer to MC portal's I/O object
.IP "cmd_flags" 12
Command flags; one or more of 'MC_CMD_FLAG_'
.IP "token" 12
Token of DPNI object
.IP "ptp_cfg" 12
ptp single step configuration
.SH "RETURN"
'0' on Success; Error code otherwise.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The function has effect only when dpni object is connected to a dpmac
object. If the dpni is not connected to a dpmac the configuration will
be stored inside and applied when connection is made.
